                <td class="chblue"><font class="h1font">what are the chances of another "broken" combo deck showing up at gencon?</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3"><tr><td><font class="bfont"><font class="bfont"> From: only god knows</font><BR><font class="bfont"><A HREF='/magination/resources/buzz.php'>Back to Topics List</A></font><TABLE WIDTH=100% border="0" cellpadding="6"><tr><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#A6B2F3><font class="h2font"> Name</td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' bgcolor=#A6B2F3><font class="h2font"> Comment</td></tr><TR><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont"><B>Woven</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont">I would say look to Obgren. With the Creeping Chill decks coming out, I&#39;ve started to see several new ways to abuse him. Imagine how the true masters are seeing Obgren with new eyes.  </TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#A6B2F3><font class="bfont"><B>Assise18</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor=#A6B2F3><font class="bfont"> ok, as for the who too many relics thing.  As I said in an earlier post, relics are always waiting to be abused, but there are cards that stop relic heavy decks (chur, vaporize, inhibitor band with the new wording, exc...) as for broken decks, some deck always beats every deck (with the exception of janky construct, which i dont see as being likely to lose much if at all).  In my opinion, a deck becomes "broken" when you must either play it, or play a deck to beat it, or it abuses cardsplay mechanisms in ways that where never intended.<br>
Earlier in the month I put the odds of a broken deck turning up at about 65%.  After testing some things, and listening to what others are doing, I would now put it am somewhere around 85%... I think its inevatible... and just a quick comment... props to Matt Loomis and Bart Robinson for not keeping construct a secret till gencon and for showing II the problem that existed ahead of time.<br>
Later<br>
Chris Assise, Assise18 </TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont"><B>X Trime</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont">there just trying to keep the game fun by preventing broken combo decks.  cuz we all know its no fun to play againsed one of those decks </TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#A6B2F3><font class="bfont"><B>Dirt1981</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor=#A6B2F3><font class="bfont">i agree, but i also think that 2i should stop going overboard with all the MRPs, i liked the MRP for rayje&#39;s belt, its not broken anymore but is still a very powerful card, all the other MRPs made the cards unplayable as far as tournament play is concerned. </TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont"><B>X Trime</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont">I thnk interactive imagination needs to cool it on the stuff based around having looooooots of relics, or maybe even create a card that smites decks with looots of relics, because that s where all the combos come from, mainly because there usualy free to play, and give you a benefit as well </TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#A6B2F3><font class="bfont"><B>Dirt1981</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor=#A6B2F3><font class="bfont">.......<br>
<br>
with the exception of the janky construct.dec which was MRPed before i had enough time to find a way to beat it, me and my friends found that all the "broken" decks were beaten by the "right" kind of decks (usually something with chur) or even with our regular decks just by adding a few cards, or changing our play style a little.  my point is, there is no deck that can win 100% of the time, you can always design a deck that just beats a specific kind of deck. </TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont"><B>RandomAxess</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont">Well, to chime in the topic, there is a couple of very abusive decks out there that I know of.  They will make it seem like they are broken but they are beatable with the right kind of deck. </TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#A6B2F3><font class="bfont"><B>Woven</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor=#A6B2F3><font class="bfont">Rest assured, there will always be something broken lurking in the mists. Someone has found it, and someone will take it to GenCon and win. The rest of us just don&#39;t know about it yet. What is it? Who knows. </TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont"><B>Assise18</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont">I think that due to the magnitude of the event, as well as the fact that lately several decks have been comming quite close, it would be fair to put the odds of another "broken" deck being played at gencon somewhere around 65%. <br>
That being said however, I would say that there wont be anything played along the lines of the sick "Janky Construct" deck that ripped apart orgins and inspired that lately round of erratas.<br>
I think that the fact that there will be more then one strong deck will help keep things in check.  Remember, just because a deck is extrememly strong does not mean that it is broken. </TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#A6B2F3><font class="bfont"><B>Dirt1981</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor=#A6B2F3><font class="bfont">personally i think that o&#39;qua is just a broken magi, you put her and 3 bubble xyxs into any deck, and the second magi never have to get their starting cards because the rest of the deck is already in their hands.  i espically hate this combined with bograth or paradwyn decks since their strategy depends on getting plenty of cards and using one of the last two magi to set up total board control. </TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont"><B>Zelnis-Quall</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont">umm, semi-demi-likely.<br>
